: test-chaining
  ( Create array and chain mutations )
  [ 10 20 30 ]
  mut
  0 100 march.array.mut.set  ( Returns array! )
  1 200 march.array.mut.set  ( Returns array! )
  2 300 march.array.mut.set  ( Returns array! )

  ( Now array! is on stack with all modifications done )
  ( Read back values to verify )
  dup 0 march.array.at  ( Should be 100 )
  dup 1 march.array.at  ( Should be 200 )
  dup 2 march.array.at  ( Should be 300 )

  ( Stack: array! 100 200 300 )
  ( Clean up )
  drop drop drop drop
;

: main test-chaining ;
